        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Borderlands 4 Release Date Moved Up]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/borderlands-4-release-date-moved-up/1100-6531192/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/borderlands-4-release-date-moved-up.1176363/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/borderlands-4-release-date-moved-up/1100-6531192/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6531192">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Gearbox has announced a change for Borderlands 4's release date. But it's not a delay. Instead, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/borderlands-4-release-date-trailer-story/1100-6529507/" data-ref-id="1100-6529507">Borderlands 4</a> has shifted forward a few weeks and will now launch on September 12. It was previously set for release on September 23. A Sony State of Play broadcast dedicated to Borderlands 4 is coming tomorrow, April 30, at 2 PM PT / 5 PM ET.</p><p>In the State of Play, viewers can expect 20 minutes of "developer-guided gameplay, including missions, killer weapons, exciting Action Skills, new and returning characters, and more."</p><p>Borderlands 4's previous September 23 release date lined up with the launch-date for Bungie's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/marathon-everything-we-know-about-bungies-extraction-shooter/1100-6514617/" data-ref-id="1100-6514617">Marathon</a>, but the games will no longer release on the same day.</p><p>Borderlands 4 is in development for PC, Xbox, PlayStation, and <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/all-the-nintendo-switch-2-games/2900-6128/" data-ref-id="2900-6128">Nintendo Switch 2</a>. It is a sequel to 2019's Borderlands 3.</p><p>That game was 2K's fastest-selling game of all time and has shipped <a href="https://ir.take2games.com/static-files/3ae54582-44bf-4163-9024-4da314c31541" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">more than 22 million copies</a>. Borderlands 2, meanwhile, is 2K's best-selling game ever with more than 30 million units sold. In total, the Borderlands franchise has sold more than 91 million units.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
                                  </div>

          
        
  
  
                    
  
    
          
            
